race.comment: HONEY MAKER (5) is worth another chance. Winner of a similar race two back then was poised to pounce last time but got shuffled back right at a crucial point in the race and could manage only seventh. Better than that and worth another try. EVERY LITTLE THING (11) was a close-up third fresh then stayed at that trip second-up and was safely held. Freshened and has since had a nice jump-out. Sure to improve over the extra ground. SLATE RIPPER (7) has been midfield in all three this time in but should be at his top now. Has two wins at this trip and looks ready to fire. HOT CHILLI MAMA (12) has been kept fresh since a solid fourth last time and the start prior ran on well for third over a similar journey to this. Definite threat.
